tasks.description:
Create internal/hive/agentregistry_test.go with unit tests. Use standard Go testing with table-driven subtests. Every test uses t.TempDir().

Test cases:
1. TestAgentRegistry_RegisterAndGet -- register an agent, get by name, verify fields
2. TestAgentRegistry_RegisterUpdate -- register same agent twice, verify update not duplicate
3. TestAgentRegistry_GetCaseInsensitive -- register 'Nexus', get 'nexus', verify found
4. TestAgentRegistry_ListAll -- register 3 agents, list with empty filter, verify all returned
5. TestAgentRegistry_ListFilterByType -- register mixed types, filter by 'openclaw', verify
6. TestAgentRegistry_ListFilterByCapabilities -- filter by capability, verify only matching agents
7. TestAgentRegistry_ListFilterByStatus -- filter by 'idle', verify
8. TestAgentRegistry_SaveAndLoad -- register agents, save, new registry, load, verify
9. TestAgentRegistry_GetNotFound -- get nonexistent, verify nil
10. TestAgentRegistry_DiscoverOpenClaw -- create a minimal openclaw.json in temp dir with 2 agents, call DiscoverOpenClaw, verify 2 agents returned with correct types
11. TestAgentRegistry_DiscoverOpenClawMissingFile -- call DiscoverOpenClaw on nonexistent path, verify graceful error

The test openclaw.json format:
```json
{
  "agents": {
    "defaults": {
      "model": {
        "primary": "amazon-bedrock/us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1"
      }
    },
    "list": [
      {"id": "coder", "name": "coder", "workspace": "/tmp/ws-coder"},
      {"id": "producer", "name": "producer", "workspace": "/tmp/ws-producer"}
    ]
  }
}
```
